  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Meeting List Filtering & Search Interface\n\nAdd a comprehensive filtering and search system to the recorded meetings list view, enabling users to quickly surface relevant meetings from a potentially large history.\n\nRequirements:\n\nFilter Controls to Implement:\n- Date Range — filter meetings by a start and end date (presets: Today, Last 7 Days, Last 30 Days, This Month, Custom Range)\n- Duration — filter by meeting length (e.g., Under 15 min, 15–30 min, 30–60 min, Over 1 hour)\n- Participants / Attendees — multi-select filter by person name or email address extracted from meeting metadata\n- Has Action Items — toggle to show only meetings with one or more extracted action items\n- Action Item Status — filter meetings whose action items contain at least one open, in_progress, completed, or cancelled item\n- Has Transcript — toggle to show only meetings where a full transcript was ingested (vs. metadata-only records)\n- Search by Keyword — free-text search across meeting title, key points, and summary fields (distinct from the existing AI semantic search)\n- Tag / Label — if meetings support tags, allow multi-select filtering by tag\n\nBehavior & UX:\n- All filters should be combinable (AND logic) and update the meeting list in real time or on apply\n- Display an active filter summary bar showing which filters are currently applied, with individual dismiss (×) buttons per filter and a Clear All option\n- Persist applied filters in URL query parameters so filtered views are shareable and survive page refresh\n- Show a result count (\"Showing 12 of 47 meetings\") that updates as filters change\n- When no meetings match the active filters, display an empty state with a prompt to clear filters\n- Filter panel should be collapsible to preserve vertical space on smaller screens\n\nTechnical Considerations:\n- Filter state should be managed in URL params (useSearchParams / Next.js router) for shareability and back-button support\n- Database queries should apply filters server-side (not client-side JS array filtering) to handle large meeting histories efficiently\n- Add indexes on frequently filtered columns (e.g., start_time, duration) if not already present\n- Reuse or extend existing Drizzle ORM query builders for meeting retrieval\n- Ensure filter controls are accessible (keyboard navigable, ARIA-labeled)\n\nEdge Cases:\n- Meetings with missing or null duration/participant data should not be excluded by default — handle gracefully in filter logic\n- Date range filter should account for user timezone, not UTC only\n- Participant filter should normalize names/emails to avoid duplicate entries from minor formatting differences",
  "title": "Add meeting list filtering and search interface",
